# 17. ３人目

Toya: I have no intention of singing with Akito again. There's no big reason behind it, though.
Kohane: But...you always look like you're having so much fun when you sing with him...
Toya: Fun?
Kohane: Hmm?
Toya: Really? I look like I'm having fun?
An: What, you didn't even realize it?
An: To be honest, you never show much emotion. It makes it hard to tell what you're thinking.
An: But that's not the case when you're up there with Akito. I can always tell you're having fun.
Toya: .....
Toya: ...Sorry, but I've got somewhere to be.
An: Hey! You said you were free a minute ago!
Kohane: Wait, Aoyagi!
Toya: .....
Kohane: There was a time when I didn't think I'd be able to perform at an event again because I wasn't as serious about all this as the rest of you.
Kohane: But I realized that no matter what anybody told me, what I really wanted was to get back up there with An and sing!
Kohane: What is it that you really want, Aoyagi?
Toya: .....
Kohane: Oh...
Kohane: Maybe I went a little too far...
An: I'm not so sure about that. Besides, thanks to you, I think I understand him a little better.
Kohane: What?
An: I'm starting to realize he's just as stubborn as a certain other person we know.
Kohane: Other person?
An: I don't know what's going on with him, but I hope he learns to be a little more honest with himself.
An: So what do you want to do? You gonna give up?
Kohane: .....
Kohane: I want to try a bit more...
An: I thought you might say that.
An: I think this calls for a strategy meeting, then. I'll help you see this through to the end.
Kohane: Yeah!
Akito: Thanks for tonight.
New Staff: Akito, you've been doing a lot of solo shows lately. Has Toya been sick or something?
Experienced Staff: Don't bother him about it. Even the most serious musicians reach a point in their careers sooner or later.
New Staff: What?
Experienced Staff: Hey, have you confirmed the slots for tomorrow yet?
Akito: .....
Akito: Damn it...
Akito: This isn't the time to be worrying about him. I have to keep moving forward if I'm going to surpass RAD WEEKEND.
Akito: My next show is...the day after tomorrow. I need to figure out what I'm playing.
Akito: Hm? Untitled? What's this?
Akito: The hell?!
Akito: Where am I? What's going on? I don't recognize this place.
Len: Oh! You finally noticed Untitled!
Akito: K-Kagamine Len? The VIRTUAL SINGER?
Len: Huh? Is the other one not with you?
Len: Oh well, this makes three! Come on, we've got to let Miku and MEIKO know!
Akito: H-Hey! What's going on here?! Stop pulling me!
Len: Miku! MEIKO! Akito finally came!
Akito: How do you know my name?
Miku: Welcome. So you finally noticed, then.
MEIKO: So you've finally come. How lovely.
Akito: Hatsune Miku is here too? I must be hallucinating. I didn't realize I was that tired.
Len: Hey, we're no hallucination. You're Akito of BAD DOGS, aren't you?
Len: You sing with your friend, Toya...
Akito: That guy's no friend of mine!
Len: Oh!
Akito: Oh... S-Sorry...
Akito: Man... I don't know what's going on here, but Toya and I no longer have anything to do with each other.
Len: Miku, what's he talking about?
Miku: It sounds like something happened between the two of them.
MEIKO: For now, why don't you have a seat? You look simply exhausted.
Akito: Why would I hang around when I don't even know what's going on?
MEIKO: How about one cup of coffee, then? The cheesecake is pretty good as well.
MEIKO: Sometimes it's best to talk things out, don't you think?
Akito: .....
An: When did it get this late? I've got to start getting the bar ready soon.
Kohane: Oh, you're right. I should probably get going.
An's Father: Hm? Sorry, but we're not quite open yet.
Kohane & An: Hey!
An's Father: Hey there, Toya. You want your usual coffee?
Toya: No, thank you.
Toya: I... just came to say goodbye to Ken.
